properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 6 at 3:20PM AKST until February 8 at 3:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...
Winter Weather Advisory: Blowing snow expected. Winds gusting
as high as 40 mph combined with snow will bring visibilities
down to a half mile or less.
Wind Chill Advisory: Very cold wind chills expected. Wind
chills as low as 50 below zero.

* WHERE...Kuskokwim Delta. Expect the coldest wind chills and
strongest winds along the coast.

* WHEN...
Winter Weather Advisory: From 9 PM Friday to 4 PM AKST
Saturday.
Wind Chill Advisory: From 7 PM this evening to 3 AM AKST
Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Areas of blowing snow will significantly reduce
visibility. The dangerously cold wind chills could cause
frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.
